Specific Uses For Product
Boiler
  • Nests smartest, most advanced thermostat yet, the Google Nest Learning Thermostat (4th gen) is a beautiful, brilliant way to save energy, keep your home comfortable, and help make sure your heating and cooling systems are running smoothly[4]
  • Improved compatibility: It works with most 24V systems, including gas, electric, oil, forced air, heat pump, and radiant, and no C wire is required for installation in most homes; visit the Nest Compatibility Checker for more info[5]
  • Better visibility into adjustments: Asks for permission to make schedule changes to help you save energy; you'll receive notifications in the Google Home app, and you can view and accept changes with a tap[1]
  • Beautiful design: With a 60% larger display[11] and Dynamic Farsight, you can see info from across the room[1]; choose the design, like a clock or the weather; it automatically adjusts brightness for the best readability or you can adjust manually
  • Easy control in the Google Home app: Adjust on your phone from anywhere[1] or by using your voice with Alexa or a Nest smart speaker[3], its easy to install yourself and its Matter compatible for simple integration into your smart home[5]
  • Manage hot and cold spots: It comes with the Nest Temperature Sensor (2nd gen) and works with any Nest Temperature Sensor; put a sensor in any room and use the Google Home app to set the temp it should reach at a certain time of day
  • Savings you can count on: The Nest Learning Thermostat (4th gen) can help save an average of 12% on heating bills and 15% on cooling bills[2]
  • New natural heating and cooling: Your thermostat learns how the temperature outside affects the temperature inside (for example, when the sun coming through the windows will heat the house naturally) and pauses your system to help you save[1]
  • New Adaptive Eco: It uses the temperature outside to help find an energy-saving temperature when youre away and returns to a comfortable temperature within an hour of your return[1]
  • Please refer to the Legal section below for all applicable legal disclaimers denoted by the bracketed numbers in the preceding bullet points (e.g., [1], [2], etc.)

From the manufacturer

A beautiful evolution of an award-winning design.

Meet the next-gen Nest Learning Thermostat, Nests most advanced thermostat yet. It helps you save energy in smarter new ways and keeps your home comfortable.[11] And it comes in elegant finishes with premium materials.

Works with more homes than ever before

With the new 12-terminal backplate, it has expanded compatibility to work with more HVAC systems than previous generations, including humidifier, dehumidifier, and ventilation systems.[5]

Understand what is happening with your thermostat

Unlike previous generations, this thermostat can ask for permission to make schedule changes.[1] You can choose to get automatic updates or suggestions you accept or reject in the Google Home app

Natural heating and cooling puts nature to work

This new feature tracks how the temp outside affects the inside like if your home naturally warms up on sunny winter afternoons[1]. Your thermostat can pause heating to help save energy

A brilliant new design

The borderless display is 60% larger than the previous generation and has Dynamic Farsight, so you can see useful info from across the room.[1,11]

Smarter about saving energy when you're away

New Adaptive Eco finds an energy-efficient temp thats just right for your home.[1] It saves energy when you leave, and its comfy when you come back.

Better integration with your smart home

Its Matter-enabled, so it works with your favorite smart home app or voice assistant.[6] And with the Google Home app, you can adjust the temp from anywhere.[1]

Helps save energy when youre away.

Sets itself to an Eco temp when you leave, and helps make sure you come back to a comfy home.[1]

Learns when youre hot. Or not.

Smart Schedule suggests tweaks to help you save, and you can accept them in the Google Home app.[1]

Teams up with Mother Nature.

It learns how the temp outside affects the temp inside, and pauses your system to help you save.[1]

Smart is in the air.

Smart ventilation brings in fresh air when outdoor air quality is healthy and most efficient.[1,8]

Clean energy made simple.

Energy Shift from Nest Renew can automatically shift your energy use to cleaner or cheaper times.[9]

The right temp, right where you want it.

Put the included Nest Temperature Sensor in any room to help manage hot and cold spots.

See info from far away with Dynamic Farsight.

It shows you useful info you can see from across the room, like the time, weather, and more.[1]

Helps monitor your heating and cooling system.

System Health Monitor helps catch issues early. If something needs attention, it sends an alert.[4]

Control it from anywhere.

Change the temp or adjust the schedule in the Google Home app. Or just use your voice.[1,3]

Install it yourself, in 40 minutes or less.

Just follow the step-by-step instructions in the Google Home app. Or contact a Nest Pro.[5]

Compatibility

Works with most 24V systems, including gas, electric, oil, forced air, heat pump, and radiant. And with Power Sharing, theres no C wire required for installation in most homes.[5]

Customizable home screen with Dynamic Farsight

Dynamic Farsight shows you useful info you can see from across the room like a clock, the temp, weather, and more. You can choose the features you want to see.[1]

Trim Kit

Use the optional trim kit to cover any holes or unpainted areas in the wall when you install.

Nest Temperature Sensor

Put the included Nest Temperature Sensor (2nd gen) in any room to help manage hot and cold spots. The Nest Learning Thermostat (4th gen) works with any Nest Temperature Sensor.

Soli sensor

With Motion Sense, it detects activity near the thermostat to light up the display when youre close by.

Display

The borderless display is 60% larger than previous generations, and is made with a crystal acrylic lens thats durable and easy to read.[11]

    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    No C-wire needed, works well, & looks nice
    Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2024
    Color: Polished Obsidian
    Three reasons I like this product: 1) C-Wire: I don't have a c-wire available. There are VERY few modern smart thermostats that claim to work without one. I first tried one of the others, the Sensi. It did not have any apparent easy way to determine in... See more
    Three reasons I like this product:

    1) C-Wire: I don't have a c-wire available. There are VERY few modern smart thermostats that claim to work without one.
    I first tried one of the others, the Sensi. It did not have any apparent easy way to determine in advance if it would work without a c-wire. It didn't work for me. The lack of an easy advance tool cost both of us time and money; a lose/lose. A wrote a well-deserved 1 star review of that product.
    This product does have a very easy tool to determine in advance if it will work without a c-wire. It took me literally 10 seconds to use that tool & be confident this would work. And, it does, in fact, work great without a c-wire.

    2) Functionality:
    It comes with a remote temp sensor which is a new thing for me and a great idea. I put mine in the bedroom. It was crazy-easy to set up and I really like the simple interface letting you choose when & how you want the thermostat to use it. It says you can add more of these if you want.
    Programming a daily schedule is incredibly easy as is making quick adjustments to that schedule.
    It has all sorts of other features such as auto-adjusting based on who is home, learning your patterns & making further auto adjustments, accepting voice commands, and so on. I do not want to use any of those things. They made it very easy for me to just say "no thanks" to all of those things and still have a nice seamless experience.

    3) Appearance: I hesitated to buy this product because it is round while my previous thermostat was rectangular and the wall is messed up everywhere behind the area of the old thermostat. Yes, I can patch a wall and paint it - but, no, I don't really want to if I can avoid it. It was a pleasant surprise to me that this thermostat came with an optional large faceplate that is made to cover up the bad wall in exactly my situation. I used it and it is great.

    Privacy is a concern but that seems to come with just about everything these days so - I don't know - just get over it?

    I recommend this.

    1.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Terrible - won't learn correctly or stay on (Google Home is also a terrible interface)
    Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2024
    Color: Polished Obsidian
    Bought this the day it came out excited for a Gen 4 Nest to put in a new build house. Set up seemed super easy but was too good to be true, seems it didn't "learn" properly and it stopped working correctly within 36 hours (Would read "76 cooling to 72"... See more
    Bought this the day it came out excited for a Gen 4 Nest to put in a new build house. Set up seemed super easy but was too good to be true, seems it didn't "learn" properly and it stopped working correctly within 36 hours (Would read "76 cooling to 72" but the HVAC system was not actually running, just the fan). It's summer in Texas and this thermostat just does not cut it. Luckily, the house is sealed up pretty well and the insulation is brand-new or we'd sweat to death.

    Suffered through this for a couple days thinking it was still learning and/or updating software in the background but finally gave up, deleted everything, and started over with full setup process. Seemed to work but only for a day or so. Suffered for a few more days, hoping it would be learning or figure itself out, to no avail. Deleted everything, re-did setup, again. Worked for a couple days and then didn't, again.

    It also forces you to setup and interface with this thermostat through Google Home which is absolutely awful compared with the old Nest app.

    HVAC tech came out and said NESTs were over 50% of his calls, the unit wasn't properly telling the fan or cooling system what to do. HVAC system is a brand new 16-seer Goodman system that is super simple, no variable speed fans or equipment like that; just a solid, simple system. So it was not the HVAC equipment's fault.

    Since we had to wait to close on the house and then went through a couple weeks and cycles of the setup process we are outside of the return window now, so that's $400 down the drains (bought the extra sensors too, for a total of four, and only two would stay registered/recognized).

    Will never buy a Nest again.

  • Steven
    4.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Beautiful design with some flaws.
    Reviewed in the United States on August 23, 2024
    Color: Polished Silver
    My 4th Gen Nest was delivered yesterday in silver, upgraded from 3rd Gen Nest. A few first impressions: It's a beautiful device, and the mushroom-style design gives the impression that the thermostat is floating. The screen could be a... See more
    My 4th Gen Nest was delivered yesterday in silver, upgraded from 3rd Gen Nest.

    A few first impressions:

    It's a beautiful device, and the mushroom-style design gives the impression that the thermostat is floating.

    The screen could be a bit brighter. It's often hard to see smaller and shaded graphical elements. I also preferred the 3rd gen display turning blue or red when the cooling or heating was active. But I also get Google is going for a more subtle visual style.

    The Farsight clock is very nice and useful, as I walk by it constantly during the day.

    The Google Home app is dramatically worse than the Nest app. It's fidgety and just barely intuitive with a flat and dull UI. There's also no way to access it on MacOS.

    Matter support for the thermostat is terrific, but there's no support for the sensors. That's a miss. I have Starling, so I'll get support in a future update, but it's pretty frustrating that they left this out.

    Overall, a nice but slightly flawed upgrade.
